<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="391" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,417,912]" pageId="10" pageNumber="391">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,814,840]" pageId="10" pageNumber="391">Remarks.</emphasis>
The species is recorded for the first time from 
<collectingRegion box="[866,944,814,840]" country="India" name="Kerala" pageId="10" pageNumber="391">Kerala</collectingRegion>
. It was previously known only from 
<collectingRegion country="India" name="Tamil Nadu" pageId="10" pageNumber="391">Tamil Nadu</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Gates, G. E." box="[229,363,850,876]" pageId="10" pageNumber="391" pagination="487 - 518" refId="ref12401" refString="Gates, G. E. (1940) Indian earthworms XIII. The genus Moniligaster. Records of the Indian Museum, 42, 487 - 518." type="journal article" year="1940">Gates 1940</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingRegion box="[417,494,850,876]" country="India" name="Kerala" pageId="10" pageNumber="391">Kerala</collectingRegion>
, it is confined to the higher altitude shola-grassland ecosystem of Nemakkad near Munnar.
</paragraph>
